<title>USA: Encore sells systems to British airforce.</title>
<headline>Encore sells systems to British airforce.</headline>
<dateline>FORT LAUDERDALE, Florida 1997-04-08</dateline>
<text>
<p>Encore Computer Corp said it sold five of its RSX computer systems to Britain's Royal Air Force for an undisclosed sum.</p>
<p>The real-time RSX computer systems would be used to upgrade three types of RAF frontline operational aircraft simulators, the company said.</p>
<p>The flight simulators were being upgraded to provide increased modelling capacity, increased reliability, reduced running costs and commonality of equipment, it said.</p>
<p>Encore develops scalable real-time data storage, data retrieval and data sharing technologies for mixed platform processing environments.</p>
<p>--New York newsdesk 212-859-1610</p>
